r traditional gender roles. Reconstructing this 'woman's world' from fragments of cultural experience captured in written and oral sources, this book will appeal to scholars in the fields of social and cultural history, social anthropology, gender and women's studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSex rolezScotlandzShetlandxHistoryy19th century. 0aSex rolezScotlandzShetlandxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenzScotlandzShetlandxSocial conditionsy19th century. 0aWomenzScotlandzShetlandxSocial conditionsy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aBritish mainland.  aShetland women.  aculture.  ademographic factors.  aeconomic factors.  afishing.  agender relations.  ahistorical materiality.  amyth-making.  apower.  awork patterns.1 aAbrams, Lynn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779358440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847793584423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847793584/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles